文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_036_chunk1
证据片段: Post-transition corrosion data were obtained on Zircaloy-4 tubing at temperatures of 589, 616, and 633 K, and in lithium hydroxide (LiOH) concentrations that ranged from 0.001 to 0.1 molal.

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_036_chunk1
证据片段: LiOH concentrations as low as 0.01 molal (70-ppm lithium) can lead to significantly increased corrosion rates, particularly at high temperatures (633 K).

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_036_chunk1
证据片段: at moderate concentrations, 0.01 to 0.06 molal (70 to 420 ppm lithium), there is an intermediate post-transition region where the corrosion rate is only slightly greater than that typical of pure water exposures

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_036_chunk1
证据片段: Mechanically polished (abraded), stress-relief-annealed Zircaloy-4 tubing was used for this series of corrosion tests

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_036_chunk1
证据片段: Sections of tubing from six different lots were cut into ~2.0 cm-long corrosion coupons

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_036_chunk1
证据片段: coupons were subsequently corrosion tested at 589, 616, and 633 K in LiOH concentrations that ranged from 0.001 to 0.1 molal

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_036_chunk1
证据片段: All corrosion tests were performed in static Type 316 stainless steel autoclaves containing type 304 stainless steel protective liners

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_036_chunk1
证据片段: increasing the LiOH concentration from 0.0 to 0.1 molal increases the post-transition corrosion rate from 0.10 to 13.15 mg/dm²/day at 589 K
